## Verification Loop

After any significant implementation, verify before declaring done:
1. Run relevant tests (`bun test`, project-specific test commands)
2. Run typecheck/build if applicable
3. For UI changes -- visually verify
4. If no automated verification exists, state what was verified manually

Don't just write code and say "done." The feedback loop matters.

## Git Conventions

- Never commit to main -- use `feat/`, `fix/`, `wip/` branches (LAW 8)
- Private repos by default (LAW 12)
- No secrets in git -- use `.env` (gitignored) or a secrets manager (LAW 11)

